1.title: Episode #17.1
1.plot: Comedians John Bishop and Jessica Hynes join the boys and Adam dressed as Theresa May to discuss the catastrophic no deal Brexit scenario, the Liverpool accent, Boris Johnson's JCB controversy, Prince Philip's car crash and eels on coke.

2.title: Episode #17.2
2.plot: Political strategist Alastair Campbell and singer Paloma Faith join the boys to discuss the Brexit crisis as well as the latest blizzard that hit the UK. Campbell also plays the bagpipes, and Faith performs her new song.

3.title: Episode #17.3
3.plot: Velvet Buzzsaw (2019) star Zawe Ashton and comedian David Mitchell join the boys to discuss a road accident involving an octopus, the latest Brexit scandals, Liam Neeson's racist confession and - sexy seals.

4.title: Episode #17.4
4.plot: Comedian Tom Allen and actress Rosamund Pike join the boys to discuss beards, Trump, Tusk/May romance, anti-Brexit nudist, Chris Grayling's ferry scandal, Will Smith's genie, Pike's new film A Private War (2018), and Kenny G's Kardashian gig.

6.title: Episode #15.6
6.plot: Richard Ayoade joins the boys as they discuss the freak weather around the globe, global warming, flat-earthers, the 'fake Australia' conspiracy theory, the Brexit crisis, Trump, Billy Monger's "leggy", and 'ghost riding' dance challenge.

7.title: Episode #15.7
7.plot: Sara Pascoe and David Tennant join the boys to discuss if Brexit may lead to shortages, if the Paralympics should add more events, if Trump is a fascist, if funerals are expensive, Jeremy Hunt's China faux pas and Josh's leg-drinking.

8.title: Episode #15.8
8.plot: Alex loses the beard which shocks everyone. John Bishop and Joe Thomas join the boys as they discuss Boris Johnson's controversial comment about burkas, iTunes banning conspiracist Alex Jones and the U.S. Embassy's toilet paper auction.

9.title: Episode #15.9
9.plot: In the final show before summer break, Lily Allen and Caitlyn Jenner join the boys to discuss bad public behavior of Boris Johnson, Jeremy Corbyn and Trump. Inspired by Skyscraper (2018), the boys test how tough prosthetic legs really are.

1.title: Episode #16.1
1.plot: Jessica Hynes and the cheerfully tipsy birthday boy Chris O'Dowd join the boys as they talk about KGB assassins, Putin's troll army, UK's anti-gay cake shop court case, global warming, Kanye and Trump, Banksy and Gwyneth Paltrow's "Goop."

2.title: Episode #16.2
2.plot: The boys discuss Brexit, Trump, the murder of Saudi dissident journalist Jamal Khashoggi, and the papoose with Tracey Ullman and award Alex for his activism but also punish him with the global warming challenge for losing their vegan bet.

3.title: Episode #16.3
3.plot: Irreverent comedian Joe Wilkinson and dancing partners Lauren Steadman and A.J. Pritchard join the boys for this Halloween-themed episode. Topics include David Cameron's memoirs, austerity measures, Brexit, Brazil's Trump-like new president, Trump, US midterms, Assange, and Halloween costumes. They also test Alex's special new gloves for heavy lifting.

4.title: Episode #16.4
4.plot: Actress Tamsin Greig and comedian Russell Howard join the boys to discuss the 2018 U.S. midterm elections results, Trump vs. CNN's Jim Acosta, the Brexit Secretary's ignorance, mass shootings in Melbourne and California, bear cub climbing a snowy mountain to reach its mum, Bil Gates' futuristic toilet, the Mo Salah statue, and the auction of Stephen Hawking's wheelchair. Also, Alex crotch is on fire, Adam performs his diss rap track and explains U.S. politics by wrestling, Russell plugs his show and asks Josh to see his sex tape, the boys play amputee football with ...

5.title: Episode #16.5
5.plot: Comedians Jimmy Carr and Kerry Godliman join the boys to discuss the thief who looks like Ross from Friends (1994), resignations in the government over the Brexit deal, poverty in the UK, Trumpy Bear and Elton John's piano Christmas ad.

6.title: Episode #16.6
6.plot: Comedian Stephen Merchant and director Taika Waititi join the boys to discuss the ineptitude of Theresa May's opponents, Boris Johnson's shoddy water cannons deal, Trump's comment on raking, and Gary Anderson's smelly darts contest.

7.title: Episode #16.7
7.plot: Rock band Mumford and Sons, comedian musician Bill Bailey and dancers A.J. Pritchard and Lauren Steadman join the boys to perform and discuss their sleeping positions, the chaotic upcoming Brexit deal vote and the largest cow in the world.

8.title: Episode #16.8
8.plot: Comedians Rosie Jones and Joe Lycett join the boys to discuss the increasingly chaotic Brexit deal vote, the sexism of French DJ asking Ada Hegerberg to twerk, a sleepy MP, and a kid YouTube star. They also sing a Christmas drinking song.

9.title: Episode #16.9
9.plot: Comedian Sue Perkins and director Kathy Burke join the boys to discuss their Dick of the Year Award nominees, Adam's broken foot, the failed Brexit deal vote, the late beefy kangaroo, a fake Russian robot, and Tynwald Mills polar bears.

10.title: Christmas Special
10.plot: Rob Delaney and Sharon Horgan of Catastrophe (2015) fame join the boys, all dressed up as Peter Pan, as they discuss their Christmas preparations, the Gatwick drone scare, the failure of the Brexit deal and other topics. They also give away the show's annual Dick of the Year Award, take pictures with the Tynwald Mills store polar bear family and Roy Wood performs.

11.title: The Last Leg of the Year
11.plot: In this 90 mins New Year's Eve special the boys take a look back at some of the most memorable moments of 2018 and peer ahead to the next 12 months. Guests include Katherine Ryan, Johnny Vegas, Richard Ayoade and Nish Kumar.

plot: Aussie comedian and amputee athlete, Adam Hills, British comedian Josh Widdicombe, UK's most famous amputee comedian Alex Brooker, and their celebrity guests provide topical commentary on the week.
